---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Espresso - About" currentPage="about">
  <main class="px-6 py-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl font-titan text-stone-900 mt-12 mb-4 uppercase">
        The Origin Story
      </h2>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-[16px] md:text-[20px] leading-relaxed font-normal mb-6">
        I'm Chris, and I actually don't like coffee. Or didn't, until one day in
        Sicily.
      </p>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-[16px] md:text-[20px] leading-relaxed font-normal mb-6">
        I drank an espresso in Etna and realized that espresso can be good—it's
        just shit in the majority of places, and most people don't have taste.
      </p>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-[16px] md:text-[20px] leading-relaxed font-normal mb-6">
        This is my personal ranking. It's subjective. It probably won't match
        your taste. Make your own blog.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl font-titan text-stone-900 mt-12 mb-4 uppercase">
        The Method
      </h2>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-[16px] md:text-[20px] leading-relaxed font-normal mb-6">
        I visit each place once. I taste the espresso without sugar first, then
        I add sugar (eyeballed—thinner sugar is better but harder to find).
      </p>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-[16px] md:text-[20px] leading-relaxed font-normal mb-6">
        I have no clue about coffee terminology. If I describe it like "the pit
        of hell," it means it's shit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl font-titan text-stone-900 mt-12 mb-4 uppercase">
        The Attributes
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 bg-white/50 p-6 border border-stone-200 rounded-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <span class="attribute-text">(+ POSITIVE)</span>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-tight">
            What made the espresso good. My amateur descriptions of flavors and
            textures.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <span class="attribute-text">(- NEGATIVE)</span>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-tight">
            What ruined it. The notes that pulled the score down.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <span class="attribute-text">STRENGTH</span>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-tight">
            From Weak to Strong. Completely subjective and different per person.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl font-titan text-stone-900 mt-12 mb-4 uppercase">
        What Affects The Score
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 border-l-2 border-stone-200 pl-4 py-2">
        <li class="text-sm font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-wider">
          Weather
          <span class="block font-normal normal-case text-stone-500 mt-1">
            Rain, fog, sunshine—it all changes the experience.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="text-sm font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-wider">
          My Mood
          <span class="block font-normal normal-case text-stone-500 mt-1">
            How I feel that day matters. Melancholic? Focused? It affects the
            score.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="text-sm font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-wider">
          Atmosphere
          <span class="block font-normal normal-case text-stone-500 mt-1">
            The vibe of the place. Yes, this includes whether the person making
            the coffee gave off good energy or not.
          </span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-stone-200 text-center">
      <p
        class="text-[10px] text-stone-400 font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-4"
      >
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 italic">— Chris</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
